<section class="section-tight">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="card card-pad">
      <p class="muted">Effective date: May 27, 2026</p>

      <h2 class="section-title">Information we collect</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        UD Marketing Tools is designed as a simple static website with free browser-based utilities. In normal use, many tools run directly in your browser and do not require an account. We may receive information you choose to submit through the contact form, such as your name, email address, and message.
      </p>
      <p class="section-desc">
        Like most websites, basic technical information may also be processed when you visit the site. This can include browser type, device information, pages visited, referring pages, and general usage data that helps us understand site performance and improve the user experience.
      </p>

      <h2 class="section-title">How information is used</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        Information submitted through the contact form is used to respond to questions, review feedback, investigate reported issues, and improve the website. Technical and usage information may be used to monitor performance, understand which tools and guides are helpful, and make the site easier to use.
      </p>
      <p class="section-desc">
        We do not ask users to create accounts to use the free tools. We also do not sell personal information. If a third-party service is used for forms, analytics, hosting, or security, that service may process information according to its own privacy practices.
      </p>

      <h2 class="section-title">Third-party services</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        The contact form is handled through Formspree, and the website is hosted through Cloudflare Pages. These services help receive form submissions, deliver the website, and protect site availability. If analytics or measurement tools are added, they may be used to understand traffic and improve content quality.
      </p>

      <h2 class="section-title">Your choices</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        You can choose not to submit the contact form if you do not want to share your name, email, or message. You can also control cookies and tracking preferences through your browser settings. For questions about this Privacy Policy or information submitted through the contact form, please use the Contact page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
